30/11/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Representatives of Bulgaria's power utility NEC and the Russian company Atomstroyexport sealed an agreement Wednesday (November 29th) on the construction of a second Bulgarian nuclear plant, in Belene. Earlier this year, an Atomstroyexport-led consortium won an international tender for the Belene project, beating out the Czech Skoda Alliance. (Novinar - 30/11/06; Bulgarian Government website, Darik, RIA Novosti - 29/11/06)
